# MCP Tool Patterns

## Template

```typescript
server.registerTool(
  "verkada_<verb>_<noun>",
  {
    title: "Human Title",
    description: `What it does.\n\nArgs:\n  - field (type): description\n\nReturns: shape\n\nExamples:\n  - Use when: "..."`,
    inputSchema: z.object({ /* fields */ }).strict(),
    annotations: {
      readOnlyHint: true,      // GET-style
      destructiveHint: false,  // true for deletes
      idempotentHint: true,
      openWorldHint: true,     // queries external API
    },
  },
  async (args) => {
    try {
      const client = getRequestClient();
      const data = await client.get<unknown>("/path", { /* params */ });
      return { content: [{ type: "text" as const, text: truncate(JSON.stringify(data, null, 2), CHARACTER_LIMIT) }] };
    } catch (err) {
      return { content: [{ type: "text" as const, text: `Error: ${formatError(err)}` }], isError: true };
    }
  }
);
```

## Rules

- Always use `getRequestClient()` — never instantiate `VerkadaClient` in handlers
- Use `.strict()` on Zod schemas; `.refine()` for "provide one of" fields
- `truncate()` for list endpoints; skip for small single-object responses
- `client.post(path, body)` for writes; `client.delete(path, params)` for deletes
- `org_id` is auto-injected — do not require it in tool args
- Register new modules in `src/index.ts` via `register*Tools(server)`
